          <physDesc>
            <p>Vellum, about 11 1/2 in. by 7 1/4, consisting of 172 leaves, many of which are much stained by water,and one (fol. 8) mutilated. The quires, 18 in number, are signed with letters, whilst the tenth has also the arithmetical figure(<!-- Insert arithmetical figure here -->). Each page is divided into two columns, of from 37 to 43 lines.</p>
